# .dev.vars.example — local-dev env for `wrangler dev`. Copy to `.dev.vars`
# (gitignored) and fill in. PRODUCTION secrets are set with `wrangler secret put`,
# never here. KV, D1, and the R2 corpus bucket (CORPUS) are all SIMULATED locally by
# `wrangler dev` — there is no GitHub App or data repo on the data path (the authored
# corpus lives in R2). Seed the local corpus with, e.g.:
#   npx wrangler r2 object put yamp-corpus/recipes/<slug>.md --file <path> --local

# --- Secrets ---
# Kroger public-tier client_credentials app (search / flyer / prices, and the
# user-context fallback when KROGER_OAUTH_* are unset).
KROGER_CLIENT_ID=""
KROGER_CLIENT_SECRET=""

# Optional: a separate Kroger authorization_code app for cart writes. When unset,
# the cart flow falls back to KROGER_CLIENT_ID/SECRET above.
# KROGER_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=""
# KROGER_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=""

# --- Workers AI (semantic-meal-plan) ---
# The `AI` binding needs no secret here: in `wrangler dev` it proxies to the real
# Workers AI API using your wrangler login (or CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN in the env).
# Nothing to set — listed only so the binding's dev requirement is discoverable.

# --- AGPL §13 source offer (open-source-license) ---
# The source URL the open /source page links to. Leave UNSET for the normal self-hosting flow: a
# data repo created from the template runs this code unmodified, so the upstream repo (the default)
# already is the corresponding source — you set nothing. Set this ONLY if you run a genuine FORK
# with your own code changes, to point /source at your modified source. Non-secret.
# SOURCE_URL="https://github.com/you/your-yet-another-meal-planner-fork"

# --- Operator admin panel (operator-admin) ---
# In production, /admin is gated by Cloudflare Access; set the team domain + the
# Access application's AUD tag (both non-secret identifiers) to enable + verify it.
# Unset → /admin is 404 (opt-in, fails closed).
# ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN="yourteam.cloudflareaccess.com"
# ACCESS_AUD="<access-application-aud-tag>"
# Optional defense-in-depth: restrict /admin to specific operator emails (the verified
# Access `email` claim must match, case-insensitive). Unset → any valid Access session admits.
# ACCESS_ALLOWED_EMAILS="you@example.com"
# Local dev ONLY: serve /admin without Access verification so `wrangler dev` can run the
# panel. Honored only when the request host is loopback AND the ACCESS_* vars are unset; it is
# inert (panel stays 404) on any deployed host, so never set it in prod. Note: with this on,
# /health reports the admin gate as `exposed` (expected locally).
ADMIN_DEV_BYPASS="1"

# Optional: the tenant id (allowlisted username) the Members roster badges "owner". A plain,
# non-secret var (not inferred from onboarding order) — unset means no member is shown as owner.
# OWNER_TENANT_ID="casey"

# --- Connect-to-Claude modal (connect-modal) ---
# Optional, non-secret operator identity the member app's Connect-to-Claude modal templates
# into its setup steps. In production MARKETPLACE_REPO is stamped automatically by the deploy
# (the data repo IS the marketplace) and OPERATOR_NAME falls back to OWNER_TENANT_ID; set them
# here only to see templated copy in local dev. Unset, the modal shows generic copy.
# OPERATOR_NAME="casey"
# MARKETPLACE_REPO="you/yet-another-meal-planner-deployment"
# Optional Instacart Marketplace handoff. Both are required; without them it is disabled.
# Get a development key from Instacart Developer Platform. Never commit a real key.
INSTACART_API_KEY=
INSTACART_API_ENV=development
